After removing an Issue Security Scheme from a project, some issues are still not accessible by all users due to some left overs in the database. 
Although we can't replicate it, it seems to happen when an Issue Security Scheme is added to a large project, and removed right afterwards.

The available workaround is to update the "security" attribute for all issues in the project directly in the database (for OnDemand instances, file a support ticket):
{noformat}
update jiraissue set security = null where project = <pid>
{noformat}

