Using latest SDK, I've created a simple workflow plugin (post function) in JIRA, which creates a new project if certain conditions are met. The problem is, while testing the code, I accidentally made two transitions, effectively creating a new project (with the same project key) two times. Both projects exist without any problem, although they have the same project key? Further more, for testing, I've created 4-5 such projects, without any complaints from JIRA. Is that a bug or a feature? :)

Here is the code used:

{code:title=test code|borderStyle=solid}
private void createNewProjectFromIssue(Issue issue)
{
	Project p = ComponentAccessor.getProjectManager().createProject("summary", "TESTKEY", "description", issue.getAssigneeId(), "", AssigneeTypes.PROJECT_LEAD);
	ComponentAccessor.getPermissionSchemeManager().addDefaultSchemeToProject(p);
	ComponentAccessor.getIssueTypeScreenSchemeManager().addSchemeAssociation(p, ComponentAccessor.getIssueTypeScreenSchemeManager().getDefaultScheme());
	ComponentAccessor.getProjectManager().refresh();
}
{code}

